The paper describes an automated process for generating code for control systems, which involves the use of formal analysis methods and domain-specific knowledge. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a graphical dataflow language and annotations, which suggests that it may also be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of certificates to guarantee correctness, which suggests that it may also be relevant to Emerging Technologies (cs.ET).
